Class AbstractParser

java.lang.Object
ie.atu.sw.AbstractParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
Parsable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BookParser, DictionaryParser, Google1000Parser
public abstract class AbstractParser extends Object implements Parsable
Abstract class that implements the Parsable interface and is to be used by any class that parses text.

  • Method Details

    • parse

      public void parse(String file) throws Exception

      Reads all lines from the text file as a stream. For each line of text, passes it to the process() method via its own virtual thread.

      Big O Running Time: O(n). Rationale: the process() method is called for each line of text => O(n).

      Code derived from Advanced Object Oriented Programming, Week 12, LevenshteinVirtualThreads.java.

      Specified by:
      parse in interface Parsable
      Parameters:
      file - The specified text file.
      Throws:
      Exception
